# Git merge attributes
#
# We intentionally pin .gitignore to the "ours" merge strategy because an
# auto-commit process in the Emergent sandbox repeatedly appends duplicated
# "-e # Environment and credential files" blocks to it (a stray `echo -e`
# bug). Every Sandbox → GitHub sync produced a fresh merge conflict on this
# file. With `merge=ours`, the GitHub side wins on every merge — the clean
# version stays clean.
#
# The sandbox's duplicated lines are harmless anyway (just repeat the same
# rules), so we don't need them on main.
.gitignore merge=ours
